<DocsLayout title="CI Integration">
  <h1>CI Integration</h1>
  <p>EntDB ships three CLI commands that run in your CI pipeline. Together they guarantee schema safety, GDPR compliance, and backward compatibility.</p>

  <h2>The Three Commands</h2>
  <Code code={`# 1. LINT — catch schema mistakes (missing data_policy, unmarked PII, etc.)
entdb lint schema.proto

# 2. CHECK — block breaking changes (removed fields, changed types, etc.)
entdb check schema.proto --baseline .entdb/snapshot.json

# 3. GENERATE — produce typed code for Python and Go
entdb generate schema.proto --python myapp/schema.py --go pkg/schema/types.go`} lang="plaintext" />

  <h2>GitHub Actions Setup</h2>
  <Code code={`# .github/workflows/ci.yml
name: CI
on: [push, pull_request]

jobs:
  schema:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5
        with:
          python-version: "3.12"
      - run: pip install entdb-sdk

      # Step 1: Lint — catches GDPR/ACL mistakes
      - name: Schema lint
        run: entdb lint schema.proto
        # Fails if: missing data_policy, unmarked PII fields,
        # FINANCIAL without legal_basis, etc.

      # Step 2: Check — blocks breaking changes
      - name: Schema compatibility
        run: entdb check schema.proto --baseline .entdb/snapshot.json
        # Fails if: removed field, changed type, removed enum value,
        # changed propagate_share, etc.

      # Step 3: Generate — verify codegen works
      - name: Generate types
        run: entdb generate schema.proto --python myapp/schema_gen.py
        # Fails if: proto compilation error, codegen bug`} lang="yaml" />

  <h2>What Each Command Catches</h2>

  <h3><code>entdb lint</code> — Schema Quality Gate</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Rule</th><th>Severity</th><th>What it catches</th></tr>
    <tr><td>type_id_unique</td><td>Error</td><td>Two nodes with same type_id</td></tr>
    <tr><td>edge_id_unique</td><td>Error</td><td>Two edges with same edge_id</td></tr>
    <tr><td>type_id_nonzero</td><td>Error</td><td>type_id = 0 (proto3 default = unset)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>private_inherit_exclusive</td><td>Error</td><td>Node has both private and inherit</td></tr>
    <tr><td>financial_needs_legal_basis</td><td>Error</td><td>FINANCIAL/AUDIT without legal_basis</td></tr>
    <tr><td>data_policy_unset</td><td>Warning</td><td>No data_policy (defaults to PERSONAL)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>string_pii_unmarked</td><td>Warning</td><td>String field without pii/pii_false</td></tr>
    <tr><td>propagate_target_inherits</td><td>Error</td><td>propagate_share target is private</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h3><code>entdb check</code> — Backward Compatibility Gate</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Change</th><th>Verdict</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Add new node type</td><td>Non-breaking</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Add new field</td><td>Non-breaking</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Add new enum value</td><td>Non-breaking</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Remove field</td><td><strong>BREAKING</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Change field type</td><td><strong>BREAKING</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Remove enum value</td><td><strong>BREAKING</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Change propagate_share</td><td><strong>BREAKING</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Change from/to on edge</td><td><strong>BREAKING</strong></td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>First-Time Setup</h2>
  <Code code={`# 1. Install the SDK
pip install entdb-sdk

# 2. Initialize the baseline snapshot
entdb init schema.proto
# Creates .entdb/snapshot.json

# 3. Commit the snapshot to git
git add .entdb/snapshot.json
git commit -m "Initialize schema baseline"

# 4. Add CI workflow (above)

# From now on, every PR is checked automatically.`} lang="plaintext" />

  <h2>After Making Schema Changes</h2>
  <Code code={`# Non-breaking change (add field, add type):
# CI passes automatically. Snapshot auto-updates on next init.

# Breaking change (rare, requires migration):
# CI blocks. To proceed:
entdb snapshot --update
git add .entdb/snapshot.json
git commit -m "Accept breaking schema change: removed legacy field"`} lang="plaintext" />

  <h2>pyproject.toml Configuration</h2>
  <Code code={`[tool.entdb]
schema = "schema.proto"
snapshot = ".entdb/snapshot.json"`} lang="plaintext" />
</DocsLayout>
